# ── Stencil environment (example) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Reference for the environment variables Stencil honours.
#
# Copy this to `.env`: Stencil auto-loads a `.env` from the working directory (or
# a parent) at startup. Already-exported shell variables take precedence over the
# file, and the `--data-dir` flag overrides both. Keep your real `.env` out of
# version control (git-ignore it).

# Root of the per-model learning stores. v6 keeps each model in its own subdirectory:
#   <root>/censor/learned.json      — allow/deny tally consulted by `review`
#   <root>/censor/decisions.jsonl   — censor decision log (future censor-ML training set)
#   <root>/styling/styling.jsonl    — styling decision log (future styling-ML training set)
#   <root>/styling/profiles/        — per-document style-profile sidecars
#
# ⚠  decisions.jsonl contains REAL sensitive values. Point this at a private
#    location and never let it get committed — keep it outside any repo, or
#    git-ignore the folder.
#
# Precedence: `--data-dir <dir>` flag  >  STENCIL_DATA_DIR  >  default
# Default when unset: $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/stencil, else ~/.config/stencil
# Use an absolute path — Stencil does not expand `~`.
STENCIL_DATA_DIR=/absolute/path/to/visible/folder

# Optional per-model overrides. Each points a single model's store at an explicit directory,
# taking precedence over <STENCIL_DATA_DIR>/<model>. Useful to keep, say, the censor store
# (which holds real sensitive values) somewhere more private than the styling store.
#   Precedence: `--censor-dir`/`--styling-dir` flag  >  these env vars  >  <data_dir>/<model>
# STENCIL_CENSOR_DIR=/absolute/path/to/censor/store
# STENCIL_STYLING_DIR=/absolute/path/to/styling/store
